{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770132771,"nonce":"INBd0ouOeeomx4pzX1AMmZEbv3c=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n-Pha","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/144","origin":"github"},"title":"Agent must ask user for model identity if auto-detection fails","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen the identity script (`.agent/scripts/set_git_identity_env.sh`) returns `AGENT_MODEL=Unknown Model`, agents are currently proceeding with signatures containing \"Unknown Model\" instead of stopping to ask the user for clarification.\n\n**Example**: In Issue #142 (PR #143), commits were signed with \"Unknown Model\" when the correct model was \"claude-sonnet-4.5\".\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nIf an agent cannot auto-detect their model identity:\n1. **MUST** use `ask_user` tool to request model clarification before making any commits\n2. **MUST NOT** proceed with \"Unknown Model\" in signatures\n3. Should provide common model options as choices (claude-sonnet-4.5, gpt-4o, etc.)\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe agent instructions don't explicitly require asking when model detection fails. The `set_git_identity_env.sh` script outputs \"Unknown Model\" as a fallback, but doesn't indicate this is an error condition requiring user input.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Option 1: Update Agent Instructions (Recommended)\nAdd explicit rule to `.agent/AI_RULES.md` and `.github/copilot-instructions.md`:\n\n```markdown\n**Model Identity Requirement**:\n- If `set_git_identity_env.sh` sets `AGENT_MODEL=Unknown Model`, STOP\n- Use `ask_user` tool to request correct model identifier\n- Provide choices: claude-sonnet-4.5, gpt-4o, o1-pro, etc.\n- Only proceed after receiving valid model identity\n```\n\n### Option 2: Improve Detection Script\nMake `set_git_identity_env.sh` fail loudly when model is unknown:\n- Print warning to stderr: \"⚠️ Model detection failed - agent should ask user\"\n- Set exit code to signal detection failure\n- Agents check exit code and ask if non-zero\n\n### Option 3: Both\nCombine both approaches for defense-in-depth\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- ✅ Agent instructions explicitly require asking when model = \"Unknown Model\"\n- ✅ No commits made with \"Unknown Model\" signatures\n- ✅ Clear process documented for agents to follow\n- ✅ Example `ask_user` call provided in documentation\n\n## Impact\n\n- **Severity**: Medium - affects commit metadata quality and traceability\n- **Frequency**: Every new agent type or CLI tool that doesn't have auto-detection\n- **Scope**: All AI agents (Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, Antigravity, etc.)\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #142 - First occurrence where this friction was identified\n- #138 - Same issue may exist in earlier commits\n\n---\n**AI Signature**  \nAgent: Copilot CLI Agent  \nModel: claude-sonnet-4.5  \nContext: Self-reported friction during Issue #142 work","files":null}]}